@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title GKE Pub/Sub WebSocket Adapter - Connectivity Flow

actor "Web Client" as Client
participant "Ingress/Load Balancer" as Ingress
participant "websocketd\n(WebSocket Server)" as WebSocketD
participant "Ephemeral POSIX\nStorage\n(Memory-mapped FS)" as Storage
participant "pulltop\n(Pub/Sub Subscriber)" as PullTop
participant "Google Cloud\nPub/Sub" as PubSub
participant "Cron Job" as Cron
database "Workload Identity" as WorkloadID

== Initialization ==
PullTop -> WorkloadID: Authenticate using Workload Identity
activate PullTop
activate WorkloadID
WorkloadID --> PullTop: Authentication Token
deactivate WorkloadID

PullTop -> PubSub: Create/Connect to Subscription
activate PubSub
PubSub --> PullTop: Subscription Established
deactivate PullTop

WebSocketD -> Storage: Initialize shared storage mount
activate WebSocketD
activate Storage
Storage --> WebSocketD: Storage ready
deactivate WebSocketD

== Message Publishing and Pulling ==
PubSub -> PubSub: Messages published to topic
activate PubSub

PullTop -> PubSub: Pull messages from subscription
activate PullTop
PubSub --> PullTop: Return messages batch
deactivate PubSub

PullTop -> Storage: Write messages to JSON file
activate Storage
Storage --> PullTop: Write complete
deactivate PullTop
deactivate Storage

== WebSocket Client Connection ==
Client -> Ingress: Connect via WebSocket (ws://)
activate Client
activate Ingress
Ingress -> WebSocketD: Forward WebSocket connection
activate WebSocketD
WebSocketD --> Ingress: WebSocket handshake complete
Ingress --> Client: Connection established

== Real-time Message Streaming ==
loop Continuous message flow
    PullTop -> PubSub: Pull new messages
    activate PullTop
    activate PubSub
    PubSub --> PullTop: Message batch
    deactivate PubSub

    PullTop -> Storage: Append messages to JSON
    activate Storage
    Storage --> PullTop: Write acknowledged
    deactivate PullTop
    deactivate Storage

    WebSocketD -> Storage: Read new messages from JSON
    activate WebSocketD
    activate Storage
    Storage --> WebSocketD: Return messages
    deactivate Storage

    WebSocketD -> Client: Push messages via WebSocket
    Client --> WebSocketD: ACK
    deactivate WebSocketD
end

== File Rotation (Scheduled) ==
Cron -> Cron: Trigger scheduled job
activate Cron
Cron -> Storage: Rotate JSON output file
activate Storage
Storage --> Cron: Rotation complete
deactivate Storage
deactivate Cron

== New Client Connection (Using Buffer) ==
Client -> Ingress: New client connects
activate Client
activate Ingress
Ingress -> WebSocketD: Forward connection
activate WebSocketD
WebSocketD --> Ingress: Handshake complete
Ingress --> Client: Connected

WebSocketD -> Storage: Read recent messages from buffer
activate Storage
Storage --> WebSocketD: Return buffered messages
deactivate Storage

WebSocketD -> Client: Send buffered messages
Client --> WebSocketD: ACK
deactivate WebSocketD
deactivate Ingress

loop Continue streaming
    WebSocketD -> Storage: Read new messages
    activate WebSocketD
    activate Storage
    Storage --> WebSocketD: New messages
    deactivate Storage

    WebSocketD -> Client: Push new messages
    Client --> WebSocketD: ACK
    deactivate WebSocketD
end

== Client Disconnection ==
Client -> WebSocketD: Close WebSocket connection
activate Client
activate WebSocketD
WebSocketD --> Client: Connection closed
deactivate WebSocketD
deactivate Client
deactivate Ingress
deactivate Client

@enduml
